<br>
There are only 3 real phrases to describe something.  We obviously need to reform the broken seals, and we need to figure out how.  The only clue to &quot;uniting&quot; anything is  this &quot;hour&quot; mentioned here:<br>
<br>
While united in the hour<br>
<br>
So, it could be the hour &quot;out of time&quot;, the hour &quot;within these seals&quot;, (i cant make sense of either of those) or it could be &quot;the hour beyond light&quot;...<br>
<br>
Twilight.<br>
<br>
Twilight sea maybe ?  Or a reference to Shadowhaven, or even the grey, in perpetual twilight.  Twilight sea seems the best answer.<br>
<br>
Removing those 2 phrases, we have 7 left to work with.<br>
<br>
The next key is the word &quot;united&quot;.  Something plural had to be united.  Cant be the destroyer of the gods, its singular.  Could be the exiled, but the exiled have a verb phrase already - being returned .   So we have 2 more  phrases linked together, giving us 4 total.<br>
<br>
If united in destruction<br>
These unbreakable seals<br>
<br>
&amp;<br>
<br>
While united in the hour<br>
Beyond light.<br>
<br>
Something, however, must be doing the returning.  And where is the exiled returning ?  Only possible explanation given is &quot;outside of time&quot;.   Taking the first phrase i made, we get:<br>
<br>
If united in destruction<br>
These unbreakable seals<br>
Will return the exiled<br>
Outside of time.<br>
<br>
Now, add the twilight sea reference to the seals phrases, we get :<br>
<br>
If united in destruction<br>
These unbreakable seals<br>
While united in the hour<br>
Beyond light<br>
Will return the exiled<br>
Outside of time.<br>
<br>
I take this to mean, most likely that you must unite the broken seals in twilight sea, or another &quot;shadowy&quot; zone, to return the exiled.  What we have left of the phrases, can describe what is exiled.<br>
<br>
Within these seals<br>
Lies a power corrupt,<br>
The destroyer  of the Gods.<br>
<br>
(something evil or corrupt was locked away out of time by the seals, which are now obviously broken)<br>
<br>
So altogether now, we have:<br>
<br>
&quot;Within these seals lies a power corrupt:  The destroyer of the Gods.  If united in destruction these unbreakable seals while united in the hour beyond light will return the exiled outside of time.&quot;<br>
<br>
Of all the possible permutations i have seen, this has the least parenthetical explanatory pauses in it, and all the phrases seem to work together very well.  But what does it mean ?<br>
<br>
I think it means something in Twilight sea, or someone, can help return the destroyer of the gods to imprisonment behind the seals.   If we can figure out how to reform the seal that is obviously broken, we can lock something back that is unleashed upon the world.  Wonder what that could be?<br>
<br>
On my server, someone sure unleashed something.   They awakened the sleeper, and noone has an idea on how to lock it back away.  Maybe this is the quest to do it. <br>
<br>
If anyone is working on this quest, or any guilds, you might try looking in the Twilight sea zone.   I dont have any leads other than this:  I exp'd for a while off the aliens at the end of the river in a cave thru the underwater tunnel.   The only thing of interest besides twilight armor quest items in that hidden area was a rare spawn Vas Ren alien named Aequus or something, that dropped a REALLY crappy shield for his rarity and level.  Maybe he has some info on how to reunite the seals using an alien technology?<br>
<br>
Anyway, im sure someone out there knows twilight better than i do, maybe they know the answer here.<br>
<br>
Or, maybe ive just been staring at the 9 phrases too long, and a 50 ft talking banana would make sense at this point.<br>
<br>
-Phestus<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
